=='''<span style="font-family:Times New Roman;"><center>《 一. The Temple 》</center></span>'''==

=== <small><center>『<code> Narrative </code>』</center></small> ===
<div style="text-align: justify; padding: 5px 10px">
<span style="font-family:MEGRATH; font-size: 12px; color: white;">Perhaps, some day, we’ll dance around not fenced by reality’s roundness, but in jagged rocks of intertwined stars—memoirs of us undefined in superposition—enacted not in stone but eternal air. I was never into the fad of the abstract except when I needed an excuse to sadly swish paint and add random dots everywhere around a canvas and call it a painting so the art professor could give me a pad in the back.</span>
[[File:Japan.jpg|link=|300px|right]]
<span style="font-family:MEGRATH; font-size: 12px; color: white;">And the temple at the edge of Heaven and Hell seemed to be alike in a way. It seemed I was at the edge of the canvas, but let's move that out of the way first. Its twists and turns made it look like it took some undergraduate students to design its interior, not to mention the nightmare toxically dating its engineer: The floating structure amidst a foggy wave of gray dust, and lifeless, green shells of dead trees to pour concrete on. Her base salary has to be the maximum wage or the utmost gallantry wouldn't even be deserving of grazing upon her face. All red, spilling over concrete, rotting on the gates' bases, and turning smooth black.</span>

<span style="font-family:MEGRATH; font-size: 12px; color: white;">I gave up trying to squeeze my head in between the gates to see more of the exterior, so I just walked through again. It was windy and all even though there wasn't really any big gaps for the air outside to get in, probably because it was so long it had made itself the wind it needed to cool itself, but ironically, it became a steam pipe instead. I took off my jacket that was tightly grabbing me like a shark and headed off toward the blackness at the end of the hallway. The pale white sky shining lines of yellow, dusty sunrays on the stony pavement was getting dimmer and dimmer, so I took my kerosene antivenom and lit the colossal soundstage on fire as the lantern light danced around the wick. It was those faulty lanterns that people usually take whenever they needed something to cool off in the hallway other than the putrid, hellish tea that sometimes appear here.</span>

<span style="font-family:MEGRATH; font-size: 12px; color: white;">Wobbling and clacking, its wooden sticks supporting the undeserving craft hanging desperately as to not fall and ruin its magic. And I just ran forward into the blackness. Oh, yeah. The blackness. Pure in emptiness--holy, almost. I almost forgot to tell you that. I guess I was distracted enough to ignore a message of God. Remember about being on the edge of a canvas? It is that. The hallway just ended abruptly as if it was a lazily cropped painting and it was cut right in front of me. I tried looking at the sides but it was light-tight. When I retreated from it, it had this oddly, white, and ghostly shadow that was emitting off like clouded steam. I'd heard of this thing where some levels just cut themselves off, and if you happen to cross upon these empty sections, you just get erased basically into negatives. But nobody said anything about fog coming off of them. Because of that, I searched my bag for anything I could throw—any nook or cranny. Ouch. It was an empty can that'd been folded, with its aluminum skin spiking on its edges that were smaller than a single grain of sugar. It was of course a Coca-Cola.</span>
[[File:Masaaki-komori-v0-mLGpA X4-unsplash.jpg|link=|300px|right]]
<span style="font-family:MEGRATH; font-size: 12px; color: white;">I tiptoed my way and approached the empty space to make sure I wouldn't fall and decapitate my head, leaving my body to get eaten by the stars of the sky. It was about ten meters away from me. I slinged my hand like a propeller and let go of the can; thankfully, I landed the throw. I heard a ''Clang!'' right after it disappeared into its shadow; and that can only mean one thing. When the dust had settled, I kicked some pebbles right into the blackness, and yes, it sounded like it had fallen down a pit. Even though there was still a chance I was just hallucinating, I put my head in a way that if it would eat my entire body, it would only get my hair's tips. I don't know what made me that confident to be honest. Maybe it was pulling me into it for all I know, but it just soared more than the saturated red paint that covered the gates. It was an anomaly so to speak. If you've crossed a road for days on end, you would stop buy anything that stood out.</span>

<span style="font-family:MEGRATH; font-size: 12px; color: white;">When I thought it might get brighter, I noticed the paint beginning to fade. The air felt as though it, too, was dimming—like an internal fog trapped behind these gates. I rummaged through my backpack, hoping for a flashlight, but found none. As I approached again, the weight in my hands vanished. Had I dropped my backpack? There were no sounds, no signs of it anywhere. It was gone, like it had been swallowed by the gates, cast out into an endless void. I tried to distract myself, but the fading continued. Looking down, I noticed a mat beneath my feet. It read, "Welcome." Above it, a sign hung, "Number 666." A numbness settled over me, and my control slipped away. I found myself slipping into the second-person perspective, detached from myself. There was... the...</span></div>

<div style="background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0,0.5); margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:3px solid #FFFFFF; border-radius: 2px">
=='''<span style="font-family:Times New Roman;"><center>《 二. Ain't All <span style="color:#640200; text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #FFFFFF, 1px -1px 0 #FFFFFF, -1px 1px 0 #FFFFFF, -1px -1px 0 #FFFFFF, 1px 0px 0 #FFFFFF, 0px 1px 0 #FFFFFF, -1px 0px 0 #FFFFFF, 0px -1px 0 #FFFFFF">Blood</span> Red 》</center></span>'''==

=== <small><center>『<code> Narrative </code>』</center></small> ===
<div style="text-align: justify; padding: 5px 10px; font-family:MEGRATH; font-size: 14px; color: white;">
<br><br><br>
The walls themselves flesh<br><br><br>
Soft and mushy, pin bones prick<br><br><br>
It's bones of humans<br><br><br>
Miles and miles of solid flesh<br><br><br>
And its blood squeezed out<br><br><br>
Once its pores pressed, it's opaque<br><br><br>
More opaque than air<br><br><br>
All covered in dust; the rest...<br><br><br>
Is just harsh to breathe<br><br><br>
Fresh viscera everywhere<br><br><br>
Down solid, sides mush<br><br><br>
Down concrete, but top... nothing<br><br><br>
Down, glitter of rocks<br><br><br>
Top, ain't black, but blank like hope<br><br><br>
"No hope"'s a cliche<br><br><br>
And cliches should be removed<br><br><br>
But you need cliches<br><br><br>
They're the ones saving you here<br><br><br>
The only good break<br><br><br>
And they say, "Ain't all blood red"<br><br><br>
It's certainly true<br><br><br>
Because the ones that ain't red<br><br><br>
Make you want to shed<br><br><br>
All your maroon blood away<br><br><br>
You will feel less pain<br><br><br>
Joyful with your lighter blood<br><br><br>
But you remember<br><br><br>
Look at the top, it's all blank<br><br><br>
But hope makes you think<br><br><br>
That it's all black and not blank<br><br><br>
Remember again<br><br><br>
All those things you did back home<br><br><br>
How you stole mom's cash<br><br><br>
How you missed your chance at love<br><br><br>
The passing crushes<br><br><br>
The one who ignored your talk<br><br><br>
The one you ignored<br><br><br>
That gave everything to you<br><br><br>
And lost everything<br><br><br>
Then you end up in this place<br><br><br>
You crush the walls here<br><br><br>
All around you, all careless<br><br><br>
It's merely payback<br><br><br>
And then, you come to find out<br><br><br>
The flesh ain't solid<br><br><br>
Look, it had metamorphosed<br><br><br>
A cocoon forming<br><br><br>
Unwrap the bloody membrane<br><br><br>
Close your eyes, look down<br><br><br>
The blood seeping inside cracks<br><br><br>
And mixing with rocks<br><br><br>
And the cocoon says to you<br><br><br>
You look at its face<br><br><br>
You might see your mom, your dad<br><br><br>
You might see that crush<br><br><br>
The friend you betrayed for her<br><br><br>
The friend you betrayed<br><br><br>
For your own circumstances<br><br><br>
But does it matter?<br><br><br>
You entered on your own terms<br><br><br>
Does it bother you?<br><br><br>
Sure it does, look to the side<br><br><br>
Another cocoon?<br><br><br>
What exactly is it now?<br><br><br>
Open up and look<br><br><br>
It's only missing the skin<br><br><br>
And you see the heart<br><br><br>
And you look up, above you<br><br><br>
The void lingering<br><br><br>
And you look back at the heart<br><br><br>
Is it the same shade?<br><br><br>
It's blank but its tentacles...<br><br><br>
Reaching out to you<br><br><br>
Look at that, another one<br><br><br>
Now it's only blood<br><br><br>
Floating clumps of it surrounds<br><br><br>
Its rank skeleton<br><br><br>
Its heart darkens the blood clumps<br><br><br>
You feel it so close<br><br><br>
You look to the side again<br><br><br>
Never-ending halls<br><br><br>
You reach the last cocoon there<br><br><br>
A colorless cube<br><br><br>
It's ahead now; it ends here<br><br><br>
Some tentacles lunge<br><br><br>
You see black but it's all blank<br><br><br>
Your face gets all numbed<br><br><br>
Until only your eyes there<br><br><br>
Look up, not the heart<br><br><br>
But the face... that friend's face there<br><br><br>
The person you know<br><br><br>
The blank heart projects the guilt<br><br><br>
The wallet you stole<br><br><br>
The slap you got as a creep<br><br><br>
The corpse of the friend<br><br><br>
Stinking more than the air here<br><br><br>
Run to the cube there<br><br><br>
You can only feel and see<br><br><br>
All your body gone<br><br><br>
Your capillaries pumping<br><br><br>
Then it all darkens<br><br><br>
From maroon to mulberry<br><br><br>
Ain't all blood red, friend<br><br><br>
May be black — and that's enough<br><br><br>
And your veins turn black<br><br><br>
All in all, though, it's all blank<br><br><br>
You may be fooled, friend<br><br><br>
But one thing's ain't fooling you<br><br><br>
Are the cocoons here<br><br><br>
Succumb to it, friend, the cube<br><br><br>
Take a step inside<br><br><br>
Take off your shoes, it's polite<br><br><br>
Forever barefoot<br><br><br>
Becoming one with blankness<br><br><br>
Never put on shoes<br><br><br>
Because it's the only way<br><br><br><br><br>
The flesh can feed on pure <span style="color:#640200; text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #FFFFFF, 1px -1px 0 #FFFFFF, -1px 1px 0 #FFFFFF, -1px -1px 0 #FFFFFF, 1px 0px 0 #FFFFFF, 0px 1px 0 #FFFFFF, -1px 0px 0 #FFFFFF, 0px -1px 0 #FFFFFF">''blood''</span>.
</div></div>
